\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 1942.
\par 
\par I GENERAL COMMENTS 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4682859 1. GENERAL STATE OF CONFIDENCE AND REACTION TO NEWS }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 
\par 
\par No definite change appears to have taken place this week in the state of public confidence. Although Allied initiative in the Far East has contributed to "a certain brightening of the general scene"}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 the prospect on the industrial and home fronts is still viewed with depression. It is stated that "the possibility of defeat" is openly discussed in some quarters}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 
, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 coupled with the question: "Do we deserve to win?" From several Regions}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 
there are reports of "a certain reluctance to discuss the war"
\par 
\par Ten R.I.O.s report a demand for strong}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 
active and inspired Government leadership; an "almost pathetic gratitude" has been the main reaction to the new restrictions on clothing and fuel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 
both of which were regarded as real steps towards Total War. But "if the people's sacrifices are not capped by vigorous Government action}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 
a swing towards defeatism or communism is thought likely"
\par 
\par In five Regional reports reference is made to a sense of "frustration" and "fatalism". Such feelings}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 is suggested}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 arise from the desire for successful British military action}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 and for concrete evidence that we are really tackling war production. Dissatisfaction over production comes both from the direct experience of workers and the many stories of hold\emdash 
ups and idleness which are in circulation}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 and also from. a "lack of information about what is already being done".
\par 
\par In this connection}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 five R.I.O.s record appreciation of Lord Halifax's speech; "its impressive statement of our contribution to the war effort has won univ
ersal approval".
\par 
\par (1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{
