\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4682859 2. THE FAR EAST}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 
\par 
\par A more hopeful outlook is apparent in public feeling about the Far Eastern theatre of war.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 
R.I.O.s are almost unanimous in ascribing this mainly to the appointment of Gen
eral MacArthur as Supreme commander of the Allied Forces in the South Western pacific; "MacArthur's prestige stands higher than that of any general outside Russia". The heavy blows dealt to the Japanese Fleet are taken as evidence that "at last the Allies
 can hit and hurt the Japs". This news "has counteracted fatalistic depression caused by Allied losses in the Java Sea battle".
\par 
\par Sir Stafford Cripps' mission to India:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 Sir Stafford Cripps has receded a little from the forefront of the political picture. \'93
The magnitude of his task is appreciated}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 
but most people appear to expect him to be successful - "the one man for the-job" is a typical comment. It is hoped he will not be away for long. It is stated that the main public interest at the moment in India 
is "strategic rather than political'; though there is a general feeling that "India should got her freedom'.
\par 
\par Burma: Reduced interest in the Burma situation is reported}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 though "the news that Chinese troops are active in North Burma has been welcomed".
\par 
\par Singapore: There has been a renewal of talk about the fall of Singapore; "it's the first time in history so many men have surrendered without a fight"}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 
and it is felt that "no adequate explanation has yet been given". Among those with missing relatives}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 it is stated that "sorrow seems to stifle criticism".

\par 
\par Australia: Increasing interest in Australia is reported; the presence there of U.S. troops is welcomed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 
but there is speculation as to the real strength of these reinforcements. It is widely believed that Australia is "gravitating more and more" toward the United States}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3870068 and that she is "as good as lost to us as a Dominion". Most people who comment thus do act regard it as a disaster}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 
but rather as "a sound idea to have a permanent link between the two new countries".
\par The public are said to be "bewildered" at the acrimonious exchange of messages about Hr. Casey's appointment.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 Some regard the episode as "childish and stupid}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 considering the plight we are in"; others blame one side or the other: - 
"Why move Casey if it upset the Australians and he was doing a good job in Washington?" or "Why are the Australians making such a fuss?"
\par 
\par (1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3870068 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15957576 , }{
